First and 4th letter of string to be in capital

def func(name):
    first=name[:3]    #takes frorm starting to 3 and doesnt include index 3
    last=name[3:]     #includes 3 till end
    res=first.capitalize()+last.capitalize()
    return res

name=input()
print(func(name))
*******************************************************************

Similarly [1:10:2]-- skip every 2 numbers from 1 to 10
[::]-- all
[::-1]--reverses
